1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:36,995
{\an8}The government is dissolving the agency?

2
00:00:37,495 --> 00:00:41,583
{\an8}La Morte Bianca specifically instructed
that I'd be the one to finish him.

3
00:00:43,126 --> 00:00:45,920
{\an8}The Valtrovis are connected to syndicates.

4
00:00:46,588 --> 00:00:48,631
{\an8}Even though you changed your name,

5
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:52,385
{\an8}you're still known as Isidro Catacutan.

6
00:00:52,469 --> 00:00:55,096
{\an8}<i>What if Mikoy has a flaw?</i>

7
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:58,058
{\an8}What if he's a womanizer?

8
00:00:59,809 --> 00:01:02,395
{\an8}Yes, it's me! I know how much you miss me.

9
00:01:07,150 --> 00:01:08,276
{\an8}Dad?

10
00:01:10,236 --> 00:01:11,696
{\an8}That's right!

11
00:01:11,780 --> 00:01:15,283
{\an8}He's the perfect example
of a troublesome womanizer.

12
00:01:15,366 --> 00:01:19,662
{\an8}If only you knew the headaches
I went through with your father back then.

13
00:01:26,503 --> 00:01:28,004
{\an8}Get out!

14
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:40,892
{\an8}Huh?!

15
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:07,710
{\an8}I don't care! I don't care!

16
00:02:13,258 --> 00:02:15,385
{\an8}With this kind of beauty, you have
the audacity to cheat on me?

17
00:02:15,468 --> 00:02:16,469
{\an8}You're a demon!

18
00:02:16,553 --> 00:02:18,221
{\an8}Oh my God!

19
00:02:27,522 --> 00:02:30,108
{\an8}There are infinite possibilities
in a multiverse.

20
00:02:30,191 --> 00:02:32,861
{\an8}All I'm saying is,
if Mikoy ever does that to you,

21
00:02:32,944 --> 00:02:35,071
{\an8}then beast mode on!

22
00:02:35,655 --> 00:02:38,032
{\an8}Although I know
you wouldn't be able to do that

23
00:02:38,116 --> 00:02:39,409
{\an8}because you love Mikoy so much.

24
00:02:39,492 --> 00:02:41,411
{\an8}And don't get me wrong, my dear, okay?

25
00:02:42,203 --> 00:02:43,288
{\an8}I love your father so much,

26
00:02:43,371 --> 00:02:47,959
{\an8}but sometimes I just really want
to slice him into tiny pieces!

27
00:02:48,042 --> 00:02:49,377
{\an8}He's getting on my nerves, girl!

28
00:02:50,211 --> 00:02:51,838
{\an8}Based on my experience,

29
00:02:51,921 --> 00:02:55,091
{\an8}there's only one way for you to find out.

30
00:02:57,260 --> 00:02:58,970
- Just one.
- What?

31
00:03:17,822 --> 00:03:19,908
What I mean is,

32
00:03:19,991 --> 00:03:24,329
if you really want to know
if a man is cheating on you…

33
00:03:24,913 --> 00:03:26,748
When men start lying

34
00:03:26,831 --> 00:03:31,878
about the time that's
supposed to be for you, well…

35
00:03:31,961 --> 00:03:33,922
then he's busy with someone else.

36
00:03:35,882 --> 00:03:37,383
That's what you should
watch out for with Mikoy, okay?

37
00:03:37,467 --> 00:03:39,344
If there's missing time for you.

38
00:03:42,931 --> 00:03:43,848
Oh.

39
00:03:45,141 --> 00:03:46,226
{\an8}Where are you?

40
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:49,479
We need to meet.

41
00:03:52,398 --> 00:03:53,900
I need to prepare.

42
00:03:58,363 --> 00:04:00,240
And I need to protect my family.

43
00:04:01,324 --> 00:04:02,909
I will see you in a couple of days.

44
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:06,037
This is a hold up!

45
00:04:13,962 --> 00:04:15,630
Wait, do you have any cash?

46
00:04:16,297 --> 00:04:17,840
Man, I don't have cash.

47
00:04:18,466 --> 00:04:20,385
My wife has my wallet.

48
00:04:21,469 --> 00:04:24,722
If I were you, I'd just leave.

49
00:04:25,223 --> 00:04:26,307
Oh, really?

50
00:04:26,849 --> 00:04:27,809
Get the wallet!

51
00:04:43,491 --> 00:04:45,493
I need this tomorrow, okay?

52
00:04:45,576 --> 00:04:46,661
Okay, Mother Eagle.

53
00:04:49,372 --> 00:04:50,331
Bok.

54
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:52,667
Bok!

55
00:04:55,795 --> 00:04:58,673
What… What did that Mikoy say?

56
00:04:59,424 --> 00:05:00,341
Nothing.

57
00:05:00,842 --> 00:05:02,635
He wants to re-establish connection

58
00:05:02,719 --> 00:05:05,179
and says that he's ready
to get back into action.

59
00:05:06,472 --> 00:05:07,515
That's it?

60
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:10,685
After being gone for so long
and going radio silent,

61
00:05:10,768 --> 00:05:11,602
that's all he can say?

62
00:05:11,686 --> 00:05:13,855
He'll just say he's ready and that's it?

63
00:05:15,565 --> 00:05:17,900
May I remind you, Agent Sianong,

64
00:05:17,984 --> 00:05:20,903
that in those weeks you said
he was radio silent,

65
00:05:20,987 --> 00:05:23,614
he was also recovering
from a gunshot wound.

66
00:05:23,698 --> 00:05:26,826
So it is understandable
that during those times,

67
00:05:26,909 --> 00:05:29,078
he was not exactly
investigating things for us.

68
00:05:31,998 --> 00:05:33,666
Imagine, he was gone for weeks.

69
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:36,836
We don't know what happened
to him during that time.

70
00:05:44,177 --> 00:05:45,011
GLOBAL AGENCY FOR GOVERNMENT OPERATIONS

71
00:05:45,094 --> 00:05:47,722
Pursued him to turn against us.

72
00:05:48,556 --> 00:05:49,390
What if?

73
00:06:07,825 --> 00:06:08,868
Hey!

74
00:06:08,951 --> 00:06:11,370
Marshmallow in water!

75
00:06:14,082 --> 00:06:15,041
It's bland, huh?

76
00:06:16,084 --> 00:06:17,919
That's not a marshmallow.

77
00:06:18,419 --> 00:06:19,462
What is this?

78
00:06:21,464 --> 00:06:22,882
It's for the hands.

79
00:06:24,217 --> 00:06:25,468
That's why.

80
00:06:28,304 --> 00:06:29,222
Sorry.

81
00:06:29,931 --> 00:06:30,973
That's why it's bland.

82
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,773
So that's how it is.

83
00:07:09,137 --> 00:07:11,013
I need to laugh, right?

84
00:07:20,106 --> 00:07:22,233
Oh, yes! You already told me that!

85
00:07:22,316 --> 00:07:24,777
It was funny!
He thought it was a marshmallow.

86
00:07:26,863 --> 00:07:29,115
Like a sitcom joke.

87
00:07:29,615 --> 00:07:31,701
That I've already seen.
Don't you have anything else?

88
00:07:42,670 --> 00:07:46,007
Well, he's putting up this comical facade.

89
00:07:46,090 --> 00:07:48,384
He looks like a clown.

90
00:07:49,302 --> 00:07:50,636
Always joking around.

91
00:08:04,108 --> 00:08:05,693
Because there's a saying, right?

92
00:08:06,402 --> 00:08:09,113
That the funniest people
are the smartest ones.

93
00:08:10,907 --> 00:08:14,994
And the most cunning ones
are confident enough to look foolish!

94
00:08:45,775 --> 00:08:49,320
Mikoy doesn't need to know
who I really am.

95
00:08:49,403 --> 00:08:50,530
Dear…

96
00:08:53,199 --> 00:08:54,867
If Mikoy truly loves you--

97
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:09,090
Do you think I'm worth loving?

98
00:09:11,592 --> 00:09:15,596
Do you think I deserve
someone like Mikoy?!

99
00:09:17,265 --> 00:09:19,684
If he ever got to know who I really am?

100
00:09:19,767 --> 00:09:22,728
If he found out everything I've done?

101
00:09:23,437 --> 00:09:25,898
Would he still risk his life for me?!

102
00:09:25,982 --> 00:09:26,983
No!

103
00:09:29,527 --> 00:09:32,572
Mikoy would never love someone like me!

104
00:09:33,322 --> 00:09:36,200
So, please spare me the lecture

105
00:09:36,284 --> 00:09:39,954
about whether it's right or wrong
that I'm living a lie.

106
00:09:41,205 --> 00:09:45,960
All I know is he loves me,
and I love him so much.

107
00:09:51,716 --> 00:09:53,217
What matters is…

108
00:09:54,093 --> 00:09:55,303
that we're together.

109
00:09:57,597 --> 00:09:58,598
Dear!

110
00:10:07,273 --> 00:10:09,900
Why did you call me
and say you wanted to see me?

111
00:10:11,193 --> 00:10:14,238
Who is this they're saying is your FUBU?

112
00:10:15,197 --> 00:10:16,240
Huh?

113
00:10:16,324 --> 00:10:18,743
Oh, no, Daddy Sir, you know
that's just fake news!

114
00:10:18,826 --> 00:10:19,744
That's not true!

115
00:10:21,829 --> 00:10:23,414
And what even is that?!

116
00:10:23,914 --> 00:10:27,918
I don't even know what "FUBU" means!

117
00:10:28,002 --> 00:10:30,212
And now they're saying you have one?!

118
00:10:32,214 --> 00:10:36,010
Daddy Sir, let me assure you
none of that is true.

119
00:10:36,969 --> 00:10:41,265
You see, Daddy Sir,
my bashers are just trying to ruin me.

120
00:10:41,349 --> 00:10:42,850
Don't pay attention to them.

121
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:44,810
They're just rage-baiters.

122
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:51,442
I didn't get that from social media
or online.

123
00:10:52,026 --> 00:10:56,447
Angelito Pinagpala's father
told me about it.

124
00:10:57,031 --> 00:10:58,949
And he spoke to me personally.

125
00:10:59,575 --> 00:11:00,451
Oh?

126
00:11:00,534 --> 00:11:02,078
Look at your face.

127
00:11:03,704 --> 00:11:05,873
What he said is true, isn't it?

128
00:11:20,012 --> 00:11:21,764
He understands me.

129
00:11:21,847 --> 00:11:23,057
I understand him, too.

130
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:27,478
What I don't understand is,

131
00:11:27,561 --> 00:11:33,776
why would you tell him
very sensitive information

132
00:11:33,859 --> 00:11:36,737
about my investigation?

133
00:11:37,279 --> 00:11:39,698
First of all, you shouldn't
have been there in the first place.

134
00:11:39,782 --> 00:11:41,325
You didn't ask for my permission.

135
00:11:41,409 --> 00:11:44,412
Good thing Angelito's father came to me.

136
00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:47,915
What if he had posted that on Fishbook?

137
00:11:47,998 --> 00:11:51,877
What if he gave an interview
to the press, huh?!

138
00:12:09,061 --> 00:12:10,020
You're right.

139
00:12:15,484 --> 00:12:18,571
You also put your own life in danger.

140
00:12:28,122 --> 00:12:29,039
What?

141
00:12:29,832 --> 00:12:31,667
I didn't think it through.

142
00:12:32,376 --> 00:12:35,463
Because I love Angelito so much.

143
00:12:52,062 --> 00:12:54,815
Looks like she's been struck by lightning.

144
00:12:57,359 --> 00:12:58,611
Yes, struck by lin-czech.

145
00:12:58,694 --> 00:12:59,695
Huh?!

146
00:13:00,529 --> 00:13:02,781
Lightning! What lin-czech? Light-ning!

147
00:13:02,865 --> 00:13:05,117
Yes! Lin-czech!

148
00:13:06,202 --> 00:13:07,536
I'm tired. I don't want to argue.

149
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:09,246
Fine, she was struck by lin-czech.

150
00:13:13,709 --> 00:13:17,630
That your daughter is very much in love.

151
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:55,709
Yes, okay. I'm sorry.

152
00:14:13,060 --> 00:14:15,396
She needs to accomplish it!

153
00:14:21,277 --> 00:14:23,362
The life she chose.

154
00:14:23,445 --> 00:14:26,699
The life that will make
our daughter happy, Viktor.

155
00:14:51,098 --> 00:14:52,725
Wow, Mom!

156
00:14:52,808 --> 00:14:54,810
- Amazing!
- Chiara, my dear!

157
00:14:54,894 --> 00:14:55,936
Come here!

158
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:58,647
Teach me how to do Zumba!

159
00:14:58,731 --> 00:15:00,983
I need to lose weight, dear!

160
00:15:01,066 --> 00:15:05,988
You know me. I need inspiration
because all I've got is perspiration.

161
00:15:06,071 --> 00:15:09,450
But Mom, you're already so sexy!

162
00:15:09,533 --> 00:15:11,952
And if I'm blessed enough
to reach your age,

163
00:15:12,036 --> 00:15:16,332
I'd want to be
as beautiful and sexy as you.

164
00:15:16,415 --> 00:15:18,792
You really are something!
What a flatterer!

165
00:15:18,876 --> 00:15:20,502
You really are blessed, huh?

166
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:22,880
You sure love to chatter.

167
00:15:22,963 --> 00:15:25,466
- I don't know about you.
- Oh, by the way, where's Dad?

168
00:15:25,549 --> 00:15:30,387
Oh, he told me last night
he had something to take care of.

169
00:15:30,471 --> 00:15:34,350
It's because there's a piece of land
his parents gave him.

170
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:37,353
So he needs to fix the title
before it gets land-grabbed.

171
00:15:38,187 --> 00:15:39,355
- That would've been such a waste.
- Right?

172
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:41,732
So I just let him go.

173
00:15:41,815 --> 00:15:42,816
Oh my.

174
00:15:44,234 --> 00:15:45,653
What about Mikoy?

175
00:15:48,238 --> 00:15:49,740
Didn't he tell you?

176
00:15:50,449 --> 00:15:52,117
He went to the office.

177
00:15:53,994 --> 00:15:54,912
Huh?

178
00:15:57,373 --> 00:16:00,459
But we already discussed it.
He wasn't supposed to start working yet.

179
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:02,962
That's what I told him too,

180
00:16:03,045 --> 00:16:06,757
because that's what
we agreed on last time, right?

181
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,759
That's what I remember.

182
00:16:08,842 --> 00:16:10,678
But he said he had
something to take care of.

183
00:16:10,761 --> 00:16:12,596
So he left really early!

184
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:22,940
<i>When a man starts lying</i>

185
00:16:23,023 --> 00:16:24,984
about the time that should be for you,

186
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:27,027
then he's busy with someone else.

187
00:16:39,123 --> 00:16:41,250
<i>The only thing he won't be able</i>
<i>to hide from you</i>

188
00:16:41,333 --> 00:16:44,670
<i>is the time that's no longer yours.</i>

189
00:16:44,753 --> 00:16:46,338
<i>That's what you should</i>
<i>watch out for with Mikoy, okay?</i>

190
00:16:46,422 --> 00:16:48,257
<i>If there's missing time for you.</i>

191
00:17:25,878 --> 00:17:27,004
GLOBAL AGENCY FOR GOVERNMENT OPERATIONS

192
00:17:33,135 --> 00:17:34,261
That's enough!

193
00:17:43,020 --> 00:17:46,148
A.k.a. Sianong, for a cuter vibe!

194
00:17:52,154 --> 00:17:55,574
A.k.a. Alex, for a cooler vibe!

195
00:17:55,657 --> 00:17:57,993
This is Super Special Asset

196
00:17:58,077 --> 00:18:02,539
Michael D. Pinagpala,
a.k.a. Mikoy, for a cuter vibe,

197
00:18:02,623 --> 00:18:04,249
reporting back for duty!

198
00:18:07,377 --> 00:18:08,670
Why?

199
00:18:08,754 --> 00:18:10,339
Did you think I'm dead?

200
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:14,551
No matter how many bullets hit me,

201
00:18:14,635 --> 00:18:16,553
even if I get sprayed by a machine gun,

202
00:18:16,637 --> 00:18:18,972
or dropped with hundreds of bombs…

203
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:21,975
still alive!

204
00:18:29,233 --> 00:18:30,609
You?!

205
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:32,653
Angelito!

206
00:18:34,613 --> 00:18:35,823
I'm sorry!

207
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:40,994
This is my peace offering!

208
00:18:41,078 --> 00:18:42,287
I saw it at the mall.

209
00:18:42,371 --> 00:18:44,581
It's so cute, just like you.

210
00:18:45,082 --> 00:18:46,291
One for each for us!

211
00:18:48,710 --> 00:18:50,170
What's going on?

212
00:18:51,630 --> 00:18:52,631
Nothing.

213
00:18:52,714 --> 00:18:58,220
I'm just saying sorry
because I realized that you were right.

214
00:18:58,303 --> 00:19:03,142
That I was getting too involved
in your family matters.

215
00:19:03,225 --> 00:19:04,977
And I was interfering
too much in your life.

216
00:19:05,060 --> 00:19:06,937
So sorry!

217
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:10,941
Sorry.

218
00:19:11,024 --> 00:19:13,193
Sorry too for what I said.

219
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:17,072
Maybe we just weren't
in the right headspace that time.

220
00:19:17,865 --> 00:19:21,034
So, are we good now?

221
00:19:23,036 --> 00:19:25,747
Yes! Angelito and I are good now!

222
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:28,709
It's nothing! Just let it go.

223
00:19:29,793 --> 00:19:30,627
- Hey, Mikoy!
- Hey!

224
00:19:30,711 --> 00:19:31,545
- Wait, hold on!
- Wait!

225
00:19:31,628 --> 00:19:32,671
- What are you doing here?
- Hey!

226
00:19:32,754 --> 00:19:34,047
You bastard!

227
00:19:35,257 --> 00:19:36,216
- Mikoy.
- Mikoy!

228
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:37,718
Mikoy, what are you doing?

229
00:19:37,801 --> 00:19:39,720
What are you all doing?!

230
00:19:39,803 --> 00:19:41,096
What is he doing here?

231
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:44,516
Mikoy, can you put
that weapon down, please?

232
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:45,309
Mikoy, put your gun down!

233
00:19:45,392 --> 00:19:46,393
- Put your gun down!
- Please, can you?

234
00:19:46,476 --> 00:19:48,645
Listen to me! Believe me!

235
00:19:48,729 --> 00:19:50,063
I know this guy!

236
00:19:50,147 --> 00:19:52,232
He's the head of security of the Valtrovis

237
00:19:52,316 --> 00:19:55,319
and most likely one of Moravianos men.

238
00:19:55,819 --> 00:19:57,321
- Mikoy!
- I will never forget

239
00:19:57,404 --> 00:19:59,865
the face of this idiot!

240
00:20:01,283 --> 00:20:02,451
Mikoy, we know!

241
00:20:02,534 --> 00:20:04,786
We know his background with the Valtrovis.

242
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:06,163
- That's enough.
- Oh?

243
00:20:07,164 --> 00:20:08,248
So that's it!

244
00:20:08,749 --> 00:20:10,292
Then why did you let him in here?

245
00:20:13,879 --> 00:20:15,672
- Working for us?
- Yes.

246
00:20:15,756 --> 00:20:16,798
Since when?!

247
00:20:17,382 --> 00:20:18,217
Since when?!

248
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:20,510
Since you went on vacation leave!

249
00:20:20,594 --> 00:20:22,137
- Hey! That wasn't vacation leave!
- You were gone for days.

250
00:20:22,221 --> 00:20:23,263
That was sick leave!

251
00:20:25,307 --> 00:20:27,267
And put that down already.

252
00:20:27,351 --> 00:20:28,644
You might hit him.

253
00:20:28,727 --> 00:20:30,103
Okay, fine.

254
00:20:30,604 --> 00:20:32,606
Don't be too nervous.

255
00:20:32,689 --> 00:20:34,024
I'm not a newbie with guns anymore.

256
00:20:34,524 --> 00:20:37,277
My teacher was really good.

257
00:20:39,404 --> 00:20:42,199
And next time, lock your holster!

258
00:20:42,282 --> 00:20:44,243
It's too easy to grab your gun.

259
00:20:44,326 --> 00:20:45,327
See?

260
00:21:03,387 --> 00:21:08,141
I understand if you weren't able
to gather any intelligence,

261
00:21:08,225 --> 00:21:12,062
considering your recent shooting incident.

262
00:21:19,820 --> 00:21:20,904
Oh!

263
00:21:20,988 --> 00:21:22,239
It's nothing, sir.

264
00:21:34,376 --> 00:21:35,252
Oh gosh.

265
00:21:38,797 --> 00:21:40,674
Your mission is over.

266
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:42,759
You may leave now.

267
00:21:47,306 --> 00:21:48,432
Christy!

268
00:21:57,649 --> 00:21:58,942
{\an8}PHILIPPINE UNIVERSITY

269
00:21:59,026 --> 00:22:02,404
{\an8}You know, I'm glad we're okay now.

270
00:22:03,613 --> 00:22:07,326
Because I actually
have a favor to ask you.

271
00:22:07,409 --> 00:22:09,036
- Favor?
- Yes.

272
00:22:09,119 --> 00:22:11,747
So that's why you made up with me.
You need something.

273
00:22:11,830 --> 00:22:12,873
Hey!

274
00:22:12,956 --> 00:22:15,375
I don't ask favors often.

275
00:22:17,294 --> 00:22:18,378
All right.

276
00:22:19,296 --> 00:22:20,672
What do you need?

277
00:22:22,382 --> 00:22:25,052
I want you to meet my Dad.

278
00:22:26,178 --> 00:22:27,512
For what?

279
00:22:28,305 --> 00:22:33,060
Because I think I might have told him

280
00:22:33,685 --> 00:22:35,562
that you are my boyfriend.

281
00:22:35,645 --> 00:22:38,440
Boyfriend?! Me?!

282
00:22:38,523 --> 00:22:39,608
Yes.

283
00:22:50,118 --> 00:22:51,661
- Sir!
- Just put it there.

284
00:22:53,205 --> 00:22:54,664
What is that all about?

285
00:22:54,748 --> 00:22:56,333
Why are you firing Mikoy?

286
00:22:57,501 --> 00:23:01,004
I honestly think
we don't need Mikoy anymore.

287
00:23:11,723 --> 00:23:13,058
You know that's not true.

288
00:23:13,558 --> 00:23:15,894
Mikoy is still critical to this mission.

289
00:23:16,770 --> 00:23:19,064
Can you at least have
the decency to tell me the truth?

290
00:23:19,856 --> 00:23:22,442
Don't give me softball excuses.

291
00:23:22,526 --> 00:23:23,860
Why do you want him out?

292
00:23:23,944 --> 00:23:27,781
You know, we are under a lot of pressure.

293
00:23:33,453 --> 00:23:37,833
We have many detractors
looking for a reason

294
00:23:37,916 --> 00:23:41,128
to shut this agency down completely.

295
00:23:41,211 --> 00:23:43,463
Now, if they find out

296
00:23:43,547 --> 00:23:48,468
that we recruited
an untrained civilian as an asset,

297
00:23:48,552 --> 00:23:52,514
and Mikoy dies in the line of duty,

298
00:23:52,597 --> 00:23:53,932
that's it!

299
00:23:54,474 --> 00:23:57,394
Everything will be gone!

300
00:24:07,612 --> 00:24:09,406
Then why are you afraid of politicians?

301
00:24:12,909 --> 00:24:14,786
And this is what you'll do in return?

302
00:24:15,287 --> 00:24:17,914
You're going to remove
our most useful asset?

303
00:24:23,044 --> 00:24:25,672
If this is our final mission,
then so be it.

304
00:24:25,755 --> 00:24:29,634
I don't care if tomorrow or the next day
the government dissolves us!

305
00:24:30,218 --> 00:24:32,179
I will only do what I know is right.

306
00:24:35,515 --> 00:24:38,018
And he has already sacrificed a lot
for this mission.

307
00:24:38,101 --> 00:24:39,936
And if you take him out,

308
00:24:40,937 --> 00:24:42,689
you won't just be betraying Mikoy.

309
00:24:43,982 --> 00:24:47,485
You will also be abandoning
your principles as the agency director.

310
00:25:26,775 --> 00:25:27,901
So?

311
00:25:27,984 --> 00:25:31,071
- He didn't come to the office today?
- <i>Yes, ma'am.</i>

312
00:25:31,154 --> 00:25:34,532
Mr. Pinagpala has not yet
reported to the office.

313
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:50,131
Just relax.

314
00:25:51,383 --> 00:25:53,260
Is that Angelito?

315
00:26:01,017 --> 00:26:03,311
We believe La Fornarina
is now in the Philippines.

316
00:26:05,647 --> 00:26:06,856
What's the problem with Mikoy?

317
00:26:10,026 --> 00:26:12,737
If he betrays us, I'd be the one
who's going to kill him.

318
00:26:14,155 --> 00:26:15,407
So, how was it?

319
00:26:15,490 --> 00:26:16,741
It's okay.

320
00:26:18,368 --> 00:26:22,163
I don't like it
when someone is lying to me!

